external_knowledge:
-lowest-scoring refers to the applicant with the lowest jeemarks (marks obtained in the entrance exam); 
-highest rank based on exam performance refers to the rank assigned based on the marks (jeerank); 
-only the top result is returned, implying that if there are multiple applicants with the same lowest score and highest rank, only one of them will be retrieved.

sql:
SELECT applicant_id, jeemarks
FROM applicants
WHERE jeemarks > (SELECT AVG(jeemarks) FROM applicants);

SELECT applicants.first_name, applicants.last_name, applicants.email, preferences.pref1
FROM applicants 
JOIN preferences ON applicants.applicant_id = preferences.applicant_id;

external_knowledge:
'Top of the class' refers to the highest academic achievement, in this case, those with the highest marks and lowest rank; 
The term 'entrance exam marks' is synonymous with 'jeemarks' and 'entrance exam rank' with 'jeerank'; 
'Course preferences' refer to the applicants' choices, from pref1 to pref5, which indicate their priority for course allocation.

sql:
SELECT ec.center_name, ec.capacity AS max_capacity
FROM exam_centers ec
WHERE ec.capacity = (SELECT MAX(capacity) FROM exam_centers);

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT applicant_id) AS number_of_applicants
FROM admissions
WHERE admission_status = 'confirmed';
